Captain Cook
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:(in allusive ref. to wild pigs allegedly descended from domestic pigs released by Captain Cook, according to a longstanding tradition or legend viz. [.ho;1840 Apr 25 Sarah Mathew Journal in 1940 Founding of NZ 128 We passed numerous traces of wild pigs [in Northland], which are said to be very numerous, the descendants of those left by Captain Cook.)
